<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-08-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-08-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="195" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d195">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Sanford</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 142.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-08-25"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 25, 1864</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi>Your despatches from No. 204, of the 21st
                            ultimo, to No. 208, of the 29th ultimo, inclusive, have been received. I
                            thank you for the interesting information communicated in your No. 205,
                            relative to the movements of his Belgian Majesty. Your No. 206 was, on
                            its receipt, submitted to the perusal of the Secretary of the Navy.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Henry S. Sanford</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., <hi rend="italic">Brussels.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>